name: California
notes: California uses both O and 0 - letter 'O' with letters/personalized plates and number '0' with numbers. Standard format is #LLL### (number-letter-letter-letter-number-number-number). Source: OOS.txt compilation - requires verification with official DMV documentation. Uses 'O' with letters/personalized plates; uses '0' with numbers.

processing_metadata.description: Official California DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.character_restrictions: Uses both O and 0 - O with letters, 0 with numbers; State uses both letter 'O' and number '0'
global_rules.code_system: Information needed - research plate type code system
